Subject: [PATCH] C-8: StoplessGC root scanner (Threads/OopStorage/CLDG) on Zero

Implements StoplessHeap::scan_roots(OopClosure*) — the strong-root source the
C-9 concurrent mark/evacuate will reuse — using the standard HotSpot machinery:
  - Threads::oops_do  (thread stacks; on Zero these are the ZeroStack
    interpreterState frames + each thread's handles)
  - OopStorageSet::strong_oops_do  (JNI globals, VM-internal handles)
  - ClassLoaderDataGraph::cld_do via CLDToOopClosure  (class-loader oops +
    class mirrors / static fields)
Must run at a safepoint (asserted).

Wired through StoplessHeap::collect() which runs a VM_StoplessRootScan
VM_Operation (new VMOp_StoplessRootScan type) at a safepoint. A self-test hook
in StoplessHeap::stop() (reached at before_exit, gated by the env var
STOPLESS_ROOTSCAN_AT_EXIT — the GC_STOPLESS_FLAGS macro isn't wired into the JVM
flag table yet) runs one scan with a counting/validating closure.

RESULT on purecap Zero:
  STOPLESS_ROOTSCAN_AT_EXIT=1 java -XX:+UseStoplessGC ... -version
  [Stopless] C-8 root scan: 736 non-null roots, 32 null slots, 0 bad(tag-0)
  exit=0
i.e. the root machinery — including Zero frame walking and the safepoint VM-op
path — works on purecap; all 736 roots are valid tagged capabilities (0 tag-0).
C-8 done; unblocks the C-9 mark phase.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>

